condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Section I.A. 3 of Schedule 2 to the LA | Description :The Borrower shall maintain during the implementation ofthe Project, its offices, units and subordinated agencies with technical, environmental and social safeguards, fiduciary and otherProject related responsibilities for implementing the Project, all with powers, functions, capacity, staffing and resourcesacceptable to the Bank to fulfill their respective responsibilities under the Project. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Section I.D. 1 of Schedule 2 to the LA | Description :The Borrower, through MoTC and MA-C, shall carry out theProject in accordance with the Environmental Management Plan (EMP) and the Resettlement Policy Framework (RPF). Except as the Bankshall otherwise agree, the Borrower, through MoTC and MA-C, shall not assign, amend, abrogate or waive the EMP and the RPF or anyof their provisions. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Section I.D.2 of Schedule 2 to the LA | Description :Prior to commencement of any works to be carried out in theGrodno region under Part 1 of the Project, the Borrower shall, through MoTC and MA-C, implement the Resettlement Action Plan, inaccordance with its terms and in a manner acceptable to the Bank, including the obligation of full payment of compensation and/orthe provision of relocation to all Displaced Persons prior to any displacement. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

title.narrative: Vehicle operating costs for medium trucks, along the project road reduced
Reduction in travel time between Minsk and Grodno
Roads rehabilitated/ repaired under the project
Percentage of project beneficiaries expressing satisfaction with improved travel experiences along the project roads
Reduction in average time to complete inwards border clearance procedures (commercial vehicles) at Bruzgi BCP
Reduction in severe injuries and fatalities on road sections under this project
Development of a traffic and road safety co-ordination center (TRSCC)

target.value: TRSCC operational and providing regular road user information

title.narrative: Improved climate for SME investment in road side services

target.value: Revised market oriented framework for road side services prepared using findings from market surveys.

Implementation of the “in – channel” clearance procedures policy by State Customs Committee.

target.value: In-channel clearance policy operational with demonstrated reduction in procedures and clearance time

Improved road safety framework for the management of road construction works and wild animal road crossings
Daily road user and border crossing beneficiaries
